  "question_text": "<div class=\"paragraph\">The Cobb angle measures the angle of bend in the spine and is used to assess the severity of scoliosis.  More severe cases of scoliosis will present with larger Cobb angles.  An angle of less than <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$20$</span> degrees is considered mild, while an angle of more than <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$50$</span> degrees is considered severe.  Angles between <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$20$</span> and <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$50$</span> degrees (inclusive) are considered moderate.</div><div class=\"paragraph\">A random sample of <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$36$</span> scoliosis patients was selected and the Cobb angle for each of these patients was recorded.  The data is shown in the histogram below.</div><div class=\"u-display_flex u-justify-content_center\"><div class=\"u-display_flex u-justify-content_center u-mar-b_2\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" data-prefix=\"fas\" data-icon=\"spinner\" class=\"svg-inline--fa fa-spinner fa-pulse fa-fw fa-2x a-icon content-inherit\" role=\"img\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 512 512\"><path fill=\"currentColor\" d=\"M304 48a48 48 0 1 0 -96 0 48 48 0 1 0 96 0zm0 416a48 48 0 1 0 -96 0 48 48 0 1 0 96 0zM48 304a48 48 0 1 0 0-96 48 48 0 1 0 0 96zm464-48a48 48 0 1 0 -96 0 48 48 0 1 0 96 0zM142.9 437A48 48 0 1 0 75 369.1 48 48 0 1 0 142.9 437zm0-294.2A48 48 0 1 0 75 75a48 48 0 1 0 67.9 67.9zM369.1 437A48 48 0 1 0 437 369.1 48 48 0 1 0 369.1 437z\"></path></svg><label class=\"sr-only\"><progress></progress>Loading question supplement...</label></div></div>\n<div class=\"paragraph\">What percent of the patients in this sample had moderate scoliosis?</div>",
